Saul Niguez puts the home-side Atletico Madrid ahead with an early goal at the fourth minute against Liverpool The defending champion of Champion League struggled to stage a comeback for a better part of the match but all efforts were abortive as the first leg of their Champions League round-of-16 clash ended one goal to nil in favor of Madrid. Salah had his goal for Liverpool ruled out because Firmino miles offside. It was Oblak who made a huge mistake, sending his clearance straight to Salah.      